node.text:
Bali, and Indonesia in general, is one of my favorite places on earth. I find myself drawn back to these islands time and time again... each time capturing more of their beauty. This video is a sequel to a drone video I put together back in 2015, after a trip to Bali.
This new video, Beautiful Bali 2, is a compilation of clips shot on two different trips, in 2017 and 2018. This video does include footage from other islands near Bali as well, including East Java, The Gili Islands, Lembongan, Nusa Penida, and Ceningan. While these aren't Bali, they are close enough to visit on any trip to Bali, so I decided to include them in the video.
The video was shot on a DJI Phantom 4 Pro on the trip in 2017 and a DJI Mavic 2 Pro on the trip in 2018.
Edited in Premiere Pro.

Music: Fleeting Moment by Caleb Etheridge via Soundstripe.

Hope you enjoy! And more importantly, I hope you get the chance to visit Bali someday.

node.text: This was my 4th year doing a fall colors trip with @joshmatti on the east coast. We focused specifically on New Hampshire again this year and were once again blown away by the beauty of fall there. We were joined by the rest of my family on the trip and chased the changing colors all around the state, exploring as many backroads and hikes as we could. This is the result. 🍂🍁

node.text:
“This is where I first said I love you, and today I want to ask if I can love you forever”.

These are the words I said to @thewildindiangirl as I got down on one knee and asked my love to marry me. 
It was such a beautiful and surreal moment, a moment I still can’t believe was real.  For years I watched friend after friend find their person, wondering when I’d ever find someone for me. Years of wondering and praying to the point of almost giving up hope; only to have the pandemic make me spend time at home, creating space for @thewildindiangirl to enter into my life. 
We first met years ago in 2017 but it was this time at home that brought us together and ignited this love we now share. Almost 11 months together and it still feels like a dream. I found someone who loves me for me, my quirks and weirdness and all. She is my best friend, my adventure partner, and the person I’ll spend this lifetime exploring this big beautiful world with. 
I love you Priya Mareedu. Thank you for saying yes and making me the happiest I’ve ever been. I can’t wait to do life together forever. 

How it happened: 
After she unknowingly sabotaged my original plan, I made a backup plan, only to have that plan sabotaged by forest fires. It all worked out though as the north Oregon Coast was the only non smokey area, and a special place for us. I convinced Priya to head there to shoot some “personal content”. She is always up for an adventure, one of the reasons I love her, so she agreed and we hurried down to Canon Beach, making it to the beach only 20 minutes before sunset. From there it was a matter of setting up the tripod to take “a cute couple photo” and then secretly pulling the ring out and surprising the love of my life. I somehow kept my cool the entire day and she was completely surprised. She immediately wanted to head back home though to tell her family, so we ended up driving 10.5 hours roadtrip for 40 minutes on Canon Beach haha. It really was a a fitting proposal for us. 

❤️ August 12, 2021 ❤️

Thanks for your love and support. We are excited to plan a wedding now! :)

node.text:
Scenes from around the beautiful and diverse country of Iceland. 
My blog post from Iceland is now live! So be sure to click the link in my bio and check it out. 
In it I break down my last trip (route, cost, etc.) I also have a list of my top 20 places in Iceland as well as a map and suggested itineraries. Hope you like it 😊

node.text:
The wild rivers of Iceland.

If you look closely at the upper right of this image, you can see where this river comes from, the Hoffellsjökullan glacier. 
This glacier is an outlet glacier of Vatnajökull, the largest ice cap in Europe.

node.text:
The tradition of a birthday hike/photo continues with this shot of me at a lookout near Mount Rainier… flying the Indonesian flag, since that is where I was born, 31 years ago. 

It’s weird to look back a year ago and realize how much life can change in just one year. The pandemic certainly played a role in that and changed my lifestyle a lot this past year. I spent more time at home, and exploring in the western US. In that time at home, I fell in love with @thewildindiangirl, and started experiencing life and adventures together. This was certainly the defining change and best part of this past year ☺️ Every day is an adventure and I can’t wait to see where this next year of life takes us! 🙌🎉 
I’m believing this next year will be my best year yet 😊

node.text:
Dramatic landscapes, wild colors, and strange places. 
Just a typical Tuesday at 4am in Iceland.
